# .trivyignore — accepted / false-positive Trivy findings
#
# Format:  <CVE-ID>  [optional comment]
# Trivy picks this file up automatically when run from the repo root.
#
# To identify findings: open the PR → GitHub Security tab → Code scanning alerts
# Add the CVE-ID here with a justification, then re-run the scan.
#
# Example:
#   CVE-2024-XXXXX  # requests < 2.32: not exploitable via this app's usage pattern

# ── Add accepted findings below this line ────────────────────────────────────

# esbuild <=0.24.2 — dev server request forgery
# GHSA-67mh-4wv8-2f99 / vite 0.11.0-6.1.6 depends on vulnerable esbuild.
# Risk: only exploitable when the Vite dev server is running localhost.
# The production build outputs static files; esbuild is never shipped or
# executed server-side. Upgrading Vite requires a breaking v7 major bump.
GHSA-67mh-4wv8-2f99

# prismjs <1.30.0 — DOM Clobbering via react-syntax-highlighter
# GHSA-x7hr-w5r2-h6wg / react-syntax-highlighter 6.0.0-15.6.6 → refractor → prismjs.
# Risk: DOM Clobbering is only exploitable when user-controlled HTML is
# directly injected into the page without sanitization. This app renders
# code blocks from admin-only content, not user input.
# Fix requires upgrading react-syntax-highlighter to v16 (breaking change).
GHSA-x7hr-w5r2-h6wg
